
[1]wight

   WIGHT, n. [g., a living being. L., to live.] A being; a person. It is
   obsolete, except in irony or burlesque. [See Aught.]

   The wight of all the world who lovd thee best.

      WIGHT, a. Swift; nimble. [This seems to be a dialectical form of
                                   quick.]
